                            <comment id="12754883" author="ankur" created="Mon, 14 Sep 2009 10:04:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Is empty inputs referring to relation - l (&apos;students.txt&apos;)  or f (filter l by 1 == 2). I am seeing a similar issue where the sampler produces an empty file when the number of records in the relation being sorted in too low ( &amp;lt; 4 ). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12763776" author="pkamath" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2009 02:42:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch uses pig.inputs property from jobconf which does not directly have the input file name - it actually has a serialized arrayList&amp;lt;Pair&amp;lt;FileSpec, Boolean&amp;gt;&amp;gt; in string form containing the filespec and the issplittable flag for each input for the job - this serialized string will need to be deserialized using ObjectSerializer.deserialize and then from the filespec, the filename will need to be retrieved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
